1
00:01:02,628 --> 00:01:03,921
[alarm ringing]

2
00:01:09,988 --> 00:01:12,365
Sigh. I wish I could sleep more.

3
00:01:14,690 --> 00:01:16,327
My whole body aches.

4
00:01:16,327 --> 00:01:17,537
But it is what it is.

5
00:01:19,330 --> 00:01:20,749
I have to get up.

6
00:01:20,749 --> 00:01:21,875
[alarm ringing]

7
00:01:22,417 --> 00:01:24,044
GO TO WORK!

8
00:01:25,211 --> 00:01:26,588
I have to get moving.

9
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:31,051
Sometimes I don't even know
what day it is anymore.

10
00:01:32,343 --> 00:01:33,553
I just keep going.

11
00:01:34,637 --> 00:01:35,680
Time to work.

12
00:01:36,431 --> 00:01:37,682
[alarm ringing]

13
00:01:38,266 --> 00:01:39,267
LEAVE!

14
00:02:10,924 --> 00:02:13,426
Traffic. Driving. Passengers. Repeat.

15
00:02:15,053 --> 00:02:17,180
No time to be slow.
If you fall behind...

16
00:02:17,972 --> 00:02:18,932
you lose.

17
00:02:33,321 --> 00:02:34,239
Hello, Ma’am.

18
00:02:34,739 --> 00:02:35,824
Why did you cancel?

19
00:02:35,824 --> 00:02:37,784
I’m already here in
front of your house.

20
00:02:37,784 --> 00:02:38,576
Well, how should I know?

21
00:02:38,576 --> 00:02:40,453
The other rider got there first.

22
00:02:41,913 --> 00:02:42,914
Oh, come on, Ma’am.

23
00:02:43,113 --> 00:02:45,166
Double booking isn't right.

24
00:02:45,166 --> 00:02:48,294
I already spent time and
gas just to get here.

25
00:02:48,294 --> 00:02:50,255
You can't just leave me
hanging like this, Ma’am.

26
00:02:50,255 --> 00:02:52,090
Then next time, be faster.

27
00:02:52,090 --> 00:02:53,675
Or switch to a different
app. I don't care.

28
00:02:53,675 --> 00:02:54,801
Just stop pestering me.

29
00:02:54,801 --> 00:02:55,885
That’s not my problem.

30
00:02:55,885 --> 00:02:57,846
Or else, I’m gonna give
you a zero rating.

31
00:02:58,221 --> 00:02:59,556
I can file a report, too.

32
00:03:22,829 --> 00:03:24,013
Uncle.

33
00:03:24,038 --> 00:03:25,331
Yeah. I'm coming.

34
00:03:29,043 --> 00:03:30,003
Aunt Mercy.

35
00:03:30,336 --> 00:03:31,796
- Buddy...
- Hey, Marco.

36
00:03:31,796 --> 00:03:32,922
Put your phone away.

37
00:03:32,922 --> 00:03:33,673
Here’s your water.

38
00:03:33,673 --> 00:03:36,175
- Tinik’s kid might try to snatch that.
- Here’s your water.

39
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:38,369
My favorite customer
is here to eat.

40
00:03:38,887 --> 00:03:40,638
We’re leaving, anyway.

41
00:03:40,638 --> 00:03:42,140
The vibe around here has shifted.

42
00:03:42,140 --> 00:03:42,891
Oh, please.

43
00:03:46,352 --> 00:03:48,021
Marco, have a seat. Sit down.

44
00:03:48,021 --> 00:03:48,980
Give me a second.

45
00:03:48,980 --> 00:03:50,106
Let me just clear this out.

46
00:03:53,067 --> 00:03:54,736
Here’s your usual.

47
00:03:56,196 --> 00:03:58,406
Hot rice porridge, an egg, and...

48
00:03:58,781 --> 00:04:00,909
a cow's eye. So you can keep
a sharp eye on the road.

49
00:04:00,909 --> 00:04:02,410
- Wait. Your water.
- Thank you.

50
00:04:02,410 --> 00:04:03,828
Go on, eat up.

51
00:04:03,828 --> 00:04:05,622
I know you're exhausted from driving.

52
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:11,252
Don’t mind those two from earlier.

53
00:04:11,502 --> 00:04:12,503
It’s okay.

54
00:04:12,754 --> 00:04:14,589
They weren't lying, anyway.

55
00:04:15,506 --> 00:04:17,342
My dad really did those things.

56
00:04:17,592 --> 00:04:20,261
And I was the idiot who
followed in his footsteps.

57
00:04:20,595 --> 00:04:22,138
Marco, you were
just a kid back then.

58
00:04:22,722 --> 00:04:24,224
Yes, you made a mistake.

59
00:04:24,891 --> 00:04:26,976
But life doesn’t end there.

60
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:30,355
I see you every day.

61
00:04:30,355 --> 00:04:31,814
How hard you work,

62
00:04:31,814 --> 00:04:33,816
how well you take
care of Tonton,

63
00:04:34,609 --> 00:04:37,237
and how you chose an honest living.

64
00:04:40,073 --> 00:04:43,076
Not everyone is strong
enough to change.

65
00:04:43,868 --> 00:04:45,203
But you?

66
00:04:46,162 --> 00:04:47,538
You did it.

67
00:04:47,872 --> 00:04:48,623
Hmm?

68
00:04:50,083 --> 00:04:52,335
I’m sure your mother...

69
00:04:52,961 --> 00:04:54,629
she’d be so proud of you.

70
00:04:56,965 --> 00:04:58,091
Go on, eat.

71
00:04:58,091 --> 00:05:00,635
- I hope so, Aunt Mercy.
- I know you're tired from the road.

72
00:05:01,135 --> 00:05:02,428
[alarm ringing]

73
00:05:02,762 --> 00:05:04,180
Fetch Tonton.

74
00:05:04,222 --> 00:05:05,765
Aunt Mercy, I have to go.

75
00:05:05,765 --> 00:05:08,101
- Wait, hold on. This is for Tonton.
- I have to pick up Tonton.

76
00:05:09,143 --> 00:05:10,353
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

77
00:05:10,353 --> 00:05:11,688
- I still have to pick up Tonton.
- You're not even finished.

78
00:05:11,688 --> 00:05:12,438
That's okay.

79
00:05:12,438 --> 00:05:14,899
- Come back for the rest later!
- Will do. Thank you.

80
00:05:14,899 --> 00:05:15,984
Be careful.

81
00:05:15,984 --> 00:05:17,026
Bye.

82
00:05:33,785 --> 00:05:34,953
Is this for real, Ma’am?

83
00:05:35,336 --> 00:05:38,631
Once Tonton turns 16, he
can’t stay here anymore?

84
00:05:39,209 --> 00:05:41,044
Why is this so sudden?

85
00:05:42,260 --> 00:05:44,387
It came as a shock
to us, too, Marco.

86
00:05:44,971 --> 00:05:49,309
You know we rely solely
on donations and funding.

87
00:05:50,143 --> 00:05:53,980
That dictates how many
children we can look after here.

88
00:05:54,731 --> 00:05:56,733
I’m truly sorry it’s come to this.

89
00:05:57,525 --> 00:06:00,069
We're informing you early

90
00:06:00,069 --> 00:06:01,863
so you have time to prepare.

91
00:06:02,447 --> 00:06:04,115
I understand your situation.

92
00:06:04,782 --> 00:06:08,119
When the day comes that Tonton
can no longer stay here,

93
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:10,913
I’ll take care of him.

94
00:06:10,913 --> 00:06:12,582
Thank you so much
for all your help.

95
00:06:13,181 --> 00:06:14,807
Don’t worry, Tonton.

96
00:06:15,561 --> 00:06:17,229
You still have some time left here.

97
00:06:17,587 --> 00:06:18,880
Don’t be sad, okay?

98
00:06:19,339 --> 00:06:20,590
Thank you very much, Ma’am.

99
00:06:20,590 --> 00:06:22,467
Alright. I’ll go ahead.

100
00:06:22,467 --> 00:06:23,801
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much, Ma’am.

101
00:06:26,262 --> 00:06:27,764
Hey, don't be so down.

102
00:06:28,931 --> 00:06:30,516
Your big brother’s got this, okay?

103
00:06:31,517 --> 00:06:32,852
Don't worry too much.

104
00:06:33,227 --> 00:06:34,312
I’ll find a way.

105
00:06:34,312 --> 00:06:36,397
I can pick up extra shifts
at Aunt Mercy’s.

106
00:06:37,357 --> 00:06:38,900
I'll handle it, Tonton.

107
00:06:39,442 --> 00:06:42,236
But bro, you’re always
so tired from work.

108
00:06:42,236 --> 00:06:44,238
And now you’re adding
more to your plate.

109
00:06:44,572 --> 00:06:46,115
You might get sick.

110
00:06:46,115 --> 00:06:47,033
Whoa.

111
00:06:47,033 --> 00:06:49,160
Are you underestimating
your big brother?

112
00:06:49,494 --> 00:06:50,578
You know,

113
00:06:50,578 --> 00:06:53,539
this might be small,
but it’s strong, boy.

114
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:56,709
Besides...

115
00:06:57,251 --> 00:07:00,129
I’m actually happy we’ll be
under one roof again.

116
00:07:00,755 --> 00:07:01,798
I missed you.

117
00:07:01,798 --> 00:07:03,549
It’s been a long time
since we lived together.

118
00:07:04,175 --> 00:07:06,511
Not since Mom passed away.

119
00:07:08,029 --> 00:07:09,906
I'm sure Mom is happy too,

120
00:07:10,149 --> 00:07:11,817
now that we’ll be together again.

121
00:07:12,058 --> 00:07:13,559
So stop being so negative.

122
00:07:14,435 --> 00:07:15,353
Okay.

123
00:07:15,353 --> 00:07:17,522
If you're taking extra work
at the vulcanizing shop,

124
00:07:17,522 --> 00:07:19,690
then I'll help out at
Aunt Mercy’s eatery.

125
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:22,402
Even if they just pay
me in porridge,

126
00:07:22,448 --> 00:07:24,074
that's already a win, bro.

127
00:07:25,530 --> 00:07:28,241
You know what... you’re
really such a big eater.

128
00:07:28,866 --> 00:07:30,576
And look,

129
00:07:31,119 --> 00:07:33,454
don't worry about working.

130
00:07:33,454 --> 00:07:34,914
Let me handle that.

131
00:07:34,914 --> 00:07:36,374
Just focus on your studies.

132
00:07:36,374 --> 00:07:37,404
Let's go.

133
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:44,924
Some people have
plans for their lives.

134
00:07:44,924 --> 00:07:46,342
They have a sense of direction.

135
00:07:47,343 --> 00:07:48,344
Me?

136
00:07:48,344 --> 00:07:49,512
I just get by.

137
00:07:50,721 --> 00:07:52,557
I'm not out here chasing dreams.

138
00:07:52,557 --> 00:07:54,308
I just need to make a living.

139
00:07:57,645 --> 00:07:58,646
But that's fine.

140
00:07:58,646 --> 00:08:00,064
As long as things keep moving.

141
00:08:39,937 --> 00:08:42,273
But as fast as my days go by,

142
00:08:42,523 --> 00:08:44,066
one look from her,

143
00:08:44,442 --> 00:08:46,110
and I’m frozen in my tracks.

144
00:08:46,903 --> 00:08:48,362
I'm like an idiot.

145
00:08:48,362 --> 00:08:50,072
I can hardly breathe.

146
00:08:50,823 --> 00:08:52,533
Whenever she’s my passenger,

147
00:08:52,992 --> 00:08:55,620
I want to make every minute count.

148
00:08:57,121 --> 00:08:58,498
Ma’am, your bag.

149
00:09:00,583 --> 00:09:02,001
You're 5 minutes early,

150
00:09:02,001 --> 00:09:03,753
which means a 50-peso tip.

151
00:09:04,086 --> 00:09:05,755
I just happened to be nearby,

152
00:09:05,755 --> 00:09:07,256
so I arrived a bit early.

153
00:09:08,466 --> 00:09:10,968
It's none of my business where
you came from, Marco.

154
00:09:10,968 --> 00:09:11,844
We had a deal.

155
00:09:11,844 --> 00:09:14,805
For every minute you’re
early, you get 10-peso tip.

156
00:09:15,473 --> 00:09:16,682
So just take it.

157
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:19,185
Go on. I don’t want to
owe you anything.

158
00:09:22,104 --> 00:09:23,481
Thank you, Ma’am.

159
00:09:25,358 --> 00:09:26,359
Here, Ma'am.

160
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:28,986
I kept it loose so it won't
mess up your hair.

161
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,618
Ma’am, you missed a bit.

162
00:09:35,618 --> 00:09:36,619
I've got it.

163
00:09:39,205 --> 00:09:42,041
She looks so cute, no
matter what she wears.

164
00:09:42,708 --> 00:09:44,544
Here, Ma’am, just
like you requested.

165
00:09:45,211 --> 00:09:47,838
Fresh as can be.
No smell of sweat.

166
00:09:52,969 --> 00:09:53,761
Let me help you with that.

167
00:09:53,761 --> 00:09:54,679
No. I’ve got it.

168
00:09:56,514 --> 00:09:58,599
Let's go. I don't want to
get caught in traffic.

169
00:09:59,100 --> 00:09:59,976
I’ve got you, Ma'am.

170
00:09:59,976 --> 00:10:02,687
I discovered a new
shortcut to your office.

171
00:10:09,193 --> 00:10:11,279
Uh, Ma’am, you might
want to hold on to me.

172
00:10:11,279 --> 00:10:13,406
We’re gonna have to
speed a bit to get there.

173
00:10:13,573 --> 00:10:15,241
No. It’s fine. Just hurry up.

174
00:10:16,617 --> 00:10:18,035
Alright. If you say so.

175
00:10:26,877 --> 00:10:28,045
That hurts.

176
00:10:28,546 --> 00:10:29,839
Fine. I'll hold on.

177
00:10:30,256 --> 00:10:32,341
You can hold on as tight
as you want, Ma’am.

178
00:10:42,893 --> 00:10:45,146
I told you, Ma'am,
my shortcut worked.

179
00:10:45,521 --> 00:10:47,565
We saved ten minutes.

180
00:10:47,815 --> 00:10:48,691
Uhm...

181
00:10:48,858 --> 00:10:51,736
Ma’am, maybe you’d
like to grab a coffee first?

182
00:10:52,445 --> 00:10:53,654
No, thanks.

183
00:10:53,654 --> 00:10:56,073
I still have a lot to do. I’m busy.

184
00:10:56,407 --> 00:10:57,283
Uhm...

185
00:11:00,578 --> 00:11:02,371
Looks like I’m out of cash.

186
00:11:02,747 --> 00:11:04,874
Is it okay if I pay via e-wallet?

187
00:11:05,207 --> 00:11:07,460
It’s fine. Your tip from
earlier is enough.

188
00:11:07,877 --> 00:11:08,586
No.

189
00:11:08,586 --> 00:11:11,088
Like I said, I don’t like
owing anyone anything.

190
00:11:11,631 --> 00:11:13,633
Besides, it's done.
I already sent it.

191
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:16,010
Check it.

192
00:11:18,679 --> 00:11:19,722
Thank you.

193
00:11:20,389 --> 00:11:21,766
You should be happy

194
00:11:21,766 --> 00:11:23,976
that your hard work is
being paid fairly.

195
00:11:24,352 --> 00:11:27,438
Didn't you say you're the only
one supporting your brother?

196
00:11:27,897 --> 00:11:28,856
Yes, Ma’am.

197
00:11:29,190 --> 00:11:31,567
For the past two months,

198
00:11:31,567 --> 00:11:34,320
hiring me as your regular
rider has been a huge help.

199
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:36,113
It's guaranteed work for me.

200
00:11:36,906 --> 00:11:38,699
So instead of a tip, Ma’am,

201
00:11:38,699 --> 00:11:39,950
let’s just use it for coffee.

202
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:42,620
By my count, we still
have eight minutes.

203
00:11:43,079 --> 00:11:44,121
Come on, Ma’am.

204
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:49,543
Hey! My bag!

205
00:11:49,543 --> 00:11:50,586
Thief!

206
00:11:51,087 --> 00:11:53,047
Help! There's a thief!

207
00:11:53,047 --> 00:11:54,256
Help!

208
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,883
Marco!

209
00:11:59,512 --> 00:12:02,139
- My bag!
- Let’s just call the police!

210
00:12:07,144 --> 00:12:08,312
You bastard!

211
00:12:28,332 --> 00:12:29,291
There you go.

212
00:12:30,334 --> 00:12:31,377
- Asshole.
- Hey!

213
00:12:31,669 --> 00:12:32,628
Hey, you!

214
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:33,629
Officers, a snatcher!

215
00:12:33,629 --> 00:12:35,214
Go. He went around the corner!

216
00:12:35,214 --> 00:12:36,632
Don’t talk back.

217
00:12:36,632 --> 00:12:38,008
What do you mean,
'don't talk back'?

218
00:12:38,008 --> 00:12:39,009
- Hey, I know you.
- Marco!

219
00:12:39,009 --> 00:12:40,010
Your face looks familiar.

220
00:12:40,010 --> 00:12:41,011
- Sir! Sir! Sir!
- There are witnesses.

221
00:12:41,011 --> 00:12:41,887
- Sir! Sir! Sir!
- There's the snatcher.

222
00:12:41,887 --> 00:12:43,013
- Sir, calm down.
- It was you.

223
00:12:43,013 --> 00:12:44,390
He’s telling the truth.

224
00:12:44,390 --> 00:12:45,891
I have a video right here.

225
00:12:46,976 --> 00:12:48,018
- See? Look.
- Help! There's a thief! Help!

226
00:12:48,018 --> 00:12:50,563
It’s clear that he wasn't
the one who stole it.

227
00:12:50,563 --> 00:12:53,357
Yes, Sir. He’s not the one
who took my bag.

228
00:12:53,357 --> 00:12:55,401
- He didn't take your bag?
- No, he didn’t.

229
00:12:55,735 --> 00:12:57,027
Here’s your bag, Ma’am.

230
00:12:57,361 --> 00:12:58,320
Thank you so much.

231
00:12:58,320 --> 00:12:59,280
If it wasn’t for you,

232
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,407
- my child’s tuition money would be gone.
- Are you sure?

233
00:13:01,407 --> 00:13:02,283
Yes.

234
00:13:02,575 --> 00:13:03,534
No need, Ma'am.

235
00:13:03,534 --> 00:13:05,411
- Please take it.
- Just keep that for your child.

236
00:13:05,411 --> 00:13:06,620
Thank you.

237
00:13:07,037 --> 00:13:07,997
Alright, Ma’am.

238
00:13:07,997 --> 00:13:10,750
Please come with us to
give your statement.

239
00:13:11,083 --> 00:13:12,126
- Alright then.
- Okay, Ma'am.

240
00:13:12,126 --> 00:13:13,127
Let’s go over there.

241
00:13:14,086 --> 00:13:15,671
And you, young lady,

242
00:13:15,671 --> 00:13:17,256
better be careful.

243
00:13:17,256 --> 00:13:19,049
He’s been a hoodlum
since he was a kid.

244
00:13:23,888 --> 00:13:25,306
Marco, are you okay?

245
00:13:25,306 --> 00:13:26,348
Does anything hurt?

246
00:13:26,348 --> 00:13:27,975
No, I'm fine.

247
00:13:28,517 --> 00:13:30,186
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

248
00:13:30,644 --> 00:13:32,563
Let's go. I'm already late.

249
00:13:42,948 --> 00:13:44,366
Well, it's also on you, Marco.

250
00:13:44,366 --> 00:13:46,160
I told you not to get involved.

251
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:48,662
We should have just
called the police.

252
00:13:48,954 --> 00:13:51,290
Now look, you almost
got arrested yourself.

253
00:13:51,582 --> 00:13:53,751
Ma’am, I really do try to
stay out of trouble.

254
00:13:54,794 --> 00:13:56,670
I’m sorry you got dragged into this.

255
00:13:57,296 --> 00:13:59,131
You don’t have to apologize to me.

256
00:13:59,131 --> 00:14:00,883
I was just caught off guard.

257
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:03,719
Besides, if you hadn't
helped that woman,

258
00:14:03,719 --> 00:14:05,513
her kids would have suffered.

259
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:10,935
I'm just wondering why the
police treated you like that.

260
00:14:11,227 --> 00:14:13,395
And they called you a hoodlum.

261
00:14:13,938 --> 00:14:15,689
Why did they seem so
angry with you?

262
00:14:17,066 --> 00:14:19,026
Because my father was a criminal.

263
00:14:19,026 --> 00:14:19,819
And just like him...

264
00:14:19,819 --> 00:14:21,821
I made a mistake before.

265
00:14:22,446 --> 00:14:24,490
I trusted the wrong person.

266
00:14:25,574 --> 00:14:27,409
That’s how I got caught up in trouble.

267
00:14:28,452 --> 00:14:29,829
So, Ma’am...

268
00:14:30,329 --> 00:14:32,832
I don’t just want to say I’m sorry.

269
00:14:33,123 --> 00:14:34,792
I want to thank you, too.

270
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:37,837
Because you were
there to defend me.

271
00:14:38,671 --> 00:14:41,882
You don’t have to thank
me or apologize.

272
00:14:42,132 --> 00:14:44,426
And of course, I didn't
want you to go to jail.

273
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,637
Who else would pick me up?

274
00:14:46,929 --> 00:14:48,055
Wow. That’s so sweet.

275
00:14:49,557 --> 00:14:51,475
Shoot. I’m really late.

276
00:14:51,475 --> 00:14:52,518
Go on.

277
00:14:52,518 --> 00:14:54,228
Same time later. Don't be late.

278
00:14:54,228 --> 00:14:55,604
Thank you, Ma’am.

279
00:14:56,438 --> 00:14:57,731
I won't be late.

280
00:14:57,731 --> 00:14:59,692
Because you’re
already in my heart.

281
00:15:04,905 --> 00:15:08,033
Hand over the reports
from last quarter, please.

282
00:15:09,493 --> 00:15:10,953
Pass it to me.

283
00:15:23,549 --> 00:15:25,009
Celine! Celine!

284
00:15:25,342 --> 00:15:28,012
Look, oh my gosh.
Bali. Three days.

285
00:15:28,137 --> 00:15:30,139
It's only for 12 thousand.

286
00:15:30,598 --> 00:15:32,182
Lara, you’re so relentless.

287
00:15:32,182 --> 00:15:35,227
I told you, I can’t join you guys
on your vacations for now.

288
00:15:35,227 --> 00:15:38,480
I still have so many
student loans to pay off.

289
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:40,107
- Oh, come on, girl.
- So stubborn.

290
00:15:40,107 --> 00:15:43,402
You know, instead of getting
annoyed with Lara’s nagging,

291
00:15:43,402 --> 00:15:45,821
why don’t you just
hit up your parents?

292
00:15:45,821 --> 00:15:47,489
They’re loaded, aren't they?

293
00:15:47,489 --> 00:15:48,824
Then problem solved.

294
00:15:48,824 --> 00:15:50,993
We could be partying at the beach.

295
00:15:51,911 --> 00:15:53,287
They may have money...

296
00:15:54,038 --> 00:15:56,206
but they also have their
own families now.

297
00:15:56,874 --> 00:15:59,084
I don't want to be a bother to them.

298
00:15:59,752 --> 00:16:01,337
I can handle things on my own.

299
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:06,091
No one’s questioning what
you can do, Celine.

300
00:16:06,425 --> 00:16:08,218
Just look at that.

301
00:16:08,218 --> 00:16:10,220
You’re doing too well.

302
00:16:10,220 --> 00:16:13,641
That’s why Boss Arthur is
breathing down our necks.

303
00:16:16,435 --> 00:16:17,353
Uh...

304
00:16:17,353 --> 00:16:19,772
Well, all I'm saying is...

305
00:16:19,772 --> 00:16:22,232
you could make your life easier

306
00:16:22,232 --> 00:16:24,568
if you just asked your
parents for help.

307
00:16:24,568 --> 00:16:26,445
- Exactly.
- No.

308
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:28,197
I’d rather struggle on my own

309
00:16:28,197 --> 00:16:31,200
than ask for their help
and owe them anything.

310
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,786
Everyone! Everyone!

311
00:16:33,786 --> 00:16:35,079
Listen up.

312
00:16:36,038 --> 00:16:38,332
We have a very big problem.

313
00:16:46,340 --> 00:16:47,341
- Marco.
- Hey.

314
00:16:47,341 --> 00:16:48,550
The rent. Where is it?

315
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:50,594
You're already three
months behind.

316
00:16:50,594 --> 00:16:53,263
If you still don't have it,
I'm kicking you out.

317
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:56,976
I apologize,  Mrs. Alma.

318
00:16:56,976 --> 00:16:59,144
I’ll be cashing out later today.

319
00:16:59,144 --> 00:17:01,146
But I can only give you
one month's worth for now.

320
00:17:01,146 --> 00:17:03,357
Don't you dare try to play me!

321
00:17:03,357 --> 00:17:04,942
Nine thousand. Hand it over!

322
00:17:04,942 --> 00:17:07,444
You haven't paid in three months!

323
00:17:09,222 --> 00:17:11,099
I’m really sorry.

324
00:17:11,490 --> 00:17:12,658
Here, Ma’am.

325
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,535
Fifteen thousand.

326
00:17:14,910 --> 00:17:16,620
Two months advance.

327
00:17:17,746 --> 00:17:19,707
Go on. He’s my boy.

328
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,334
Mrs. Alma, give that back to him.

329
00:17:22,793 --> 00:17:25,295
Are you kidding?
Like I’d turn this down?

330
00:17:26,714 --> 00:17:28,632
Well, Marco? I'm waiting.

331
00:17:28,632 --> 00:17:30,718
Can’t even say thanks
to your godfather?

332
00:17:30,718 --> 00:17:32,344
I don't need your help.

333
00:17:34,179 --> 00:17:35,806
You stopped being my godfather

334
00:17:35,806 --> 00:17:37,975
the moment you sold me out.

335
00:17:37,975 --> 00:17:39,893
Marco, if I was the one who
got caught back then,

336
00:17:39,893 --> 00:17:42,855
I’d probably be looking
at twenty years in prison.

337
00:17:42,855 --> 00:17:45,357
But you? Juvenile. A minor.

338
00:17:45,357 --> 00:17:46,400
You were out in just two years.

339
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,278
That’s still two years of my life
wasted because of you.

340
00:17:49,653 --> 00:17:51,113
I’m not a kid anymore.

341
00:17:51,113 --> 00:17:52,656
You can’t play me.

342
00:17:54,283 --> 00:17:56,358
Marco, my plan was
solid back then.

343
00:17:57,536 --> 00:18:01,457
You were supposed to floor it
to draw the cops away.

344
00:18:01,457 --> 00:18:05,002
How was I to know the pawnshop
had a gun and it would go south?

345
00:18:05,002 --> 00:18:06,420
I get why you're mad.

346
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:09,131
That’s why I want to
make it up to you.

347
00:18:09,757 --> 00:18:11,467
That snatcher?

348
00:18:12,092 --> 00:18:14,390
The one you crushed?
He’s one of mine.

349
00:18:15,763 --> 00:18:18,015
You’ve still got it. No fear.

350
00:18:18,015 --> 00:18:20,059
Just like your father.

351
00:18:20,059 --> 00:18:22,561
And I need that kind of guts

352
00:18:22,561 --> 00:18:25,105
for the big business
I’m getting into.

353
00:18:27,566 --> 00:18:29,109
I’m not going back to you guys.

354
00:18:29,109 --> 00:18:32,488
Marco, no matter how much
you run from your past,

355
00:18:32,488 --> 00:18:34,114
you’re still Tinik’s son!

356
00:18:34,114 --> 00:18:36,075
It’s in your blood!

357
00:18:38,869 --> 00:18:41,705
Our international clients...

358
00:18:42,289 --> 00:18:46,460
They are starting to pull their
investments from the Philippines.

359
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:48,754
What? Why is that, Sir?

360
00:18:50,464 --> 00:18:52,925
Economic stability
of the Philippines,

361
00:18:53,592 --> 00:18:55,886
better tax breaks in
other countries...

362
00:18:56,261 --> 00:18:58,263
Whatever their reasons are,

363
00:18:58,847 --> 00:19:00,849
the bottom line is
we’re taking the hit.

364
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:03,852
But I assure you,

365
00:19:03,852 --> 00:19:06,438
your salaries for this
month will be paid.

366
00:19:07,189 --> 00:19:10,400
With all due respect to
the situation, Sir Arthur,

367
00:19:11,068 --> 00:19:13,946
we’ve been working
here for two years.

368
00:19:13,946 --> 00:19:15,531
That means...

369
00:19:15,531 --> 00:19:18,408
we’re entitled to a half-month’s
pay per year as severance.

370
00:19:18,742 --> 00:19:20,035
Of course.

371
00:19:20,494 --> 00:19:22,746
You'll get that, too.

372
00:19:23,997 --> 00:19:25,290
Actually...

373
00:19:26,041 --> 00:19:28,085
I’m leaving that to you.

374
00:19:31,421 --> 00:19:33,423
Withdraw the...

375
00:19:34,133 --> 00:19:37,094
remaining operational
funds from the bank

376
00:19:37,845 --> 00:19:41,014
so I can pay each and
every one of you.

377
00:19:42,474 --> 00:19:44,434
And one more thing,

378
00:19:44,434 --> 00:19:45,936
I want you to shred

379
00:19:45,936 --> 00:19:49,314
every piece of document in
this office for the past year.

380
00:19:50,315 --> 00:19:53,318
Erase all the data in
the system, too.

381
00:19:53,318 --> 00:19:56,071
Even the files on our hard drives.

382
00:19:56,071 --> 00:19:58,240
But why, sir?

383
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:00,492
That’s the advice from my lawyer.

384
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:02,244
Uhm...

385
00:20:02,244 --> 00:20:05,289
even if they’re no longer our clients,

386
00:20:05,289 --> 00:20:08,709
we still need to protect
their confidentiality.

387
00:20:11,503 --> 00:20:13,213
Go on, Celine.

388
00:20:13,213 --> 00:20:16,383
So you can come
back here right away.

389
00:20:16,383 --> 00:20:18,844
We still have a lot to take care of.

390
00:20:20,262 --> 00:20:21,471
I'm sorry.

391
00:20:35,694 --> 00:20:37,779
There it is. A nail.

392
00:20:38,238 --> 00:20:41,783
Good thing you caught me,
Marco. I was about to close up.

393
00:20:41,783 --> 00:20:44,077
Your Aunt Mercy and I
are going on vacation.

394
00:20:44,077 --> 00:20:46,246
It’s our anniversary.

395
00:20:46,246 --> 00:20:47,581
That’s good, Uncle.

396
00:20:47,581 --> 00:20:51,084
At your age, you deserve
a break once in a while.

397
00:20:51,084 --> 00:20:53,879
Two hundred for a patch.

398
00:20:53,879 --> 00:20:56,215
Eighty for a plug.

399
00:20:57,174 --> 00:21:01,595
But the plug won't last. It might
blow out on you on the road.

400
00:21:02,471 --> 00:21:04,181
That damn nail.

401
00:21:04,181 --> 00:21:06,350
[phone ringing]

402
00:21:08,018 --> 00:21:09,311
Hello, Ton?

403
00:21:09,770 --> 00:21:12,731
Sorry it took me this
long to answer.

404
00:21:13,106 --> 00:21:15,067
It’s been one stroke of
bad luck after another.

405
00:21:15,067 --> 00:21:16,151
Look at that.

406
00:21:16,151 --> 00:21:17,986
I even got hit by a nail.

407
00:21:18,654 --> 00:21:20,155
So, what’s up?
Why’d you call?

408
00:21:20,572 --> 00:21:22,950
It’s nothing, bro.
It’s not that important.

409
00:21:23,325 --> 00:21:24,826
Ton, I know you.

410
00:21:24,826 --> 00:21:26,620
You wouldn’t call if it
wasn't important.

411
00:21:26,620 --> 00:21:27,704
What is it?

412
00:21:29,581 --> 00:21:33,835
Well, we have a field trip.
I need five hundred to join.

413
00:21:33,835 --> 00:21:37,339
But I’ll just tell my teacher
it’s okay, I won’t go.

414
00:21:37,339 --> 00:21:38,674
No.

415
00:21:38,674 --> 00:21:40,509
It’s for your school, Ton.

416
00:21:40,509 --> 00:21:41,969
I’ll take care of it.

417
00:21:43,011 --> 00:21:44,471
Alright, bro. Thank you so much.

418
00:21:44,471 --> 00:21:46,014
Are you picking up
your crush now?

419
00:21:49,393 --> 00:21:51,186
Look at that huge smile.

420
00:21:51,186 --> 00:21:52,312
I bet she crossed your mind.

421
00:21:52,312 --> 00:21:54,898
You really like teasing
me, don't you, Ton?

422
00:21:55,274 --> 00:21:57,526
Alright. I’ll send it now.

423
00:21:57,734 --> 00:21:59,778
Man, I guess I'm busted.

424
00:22:02,114 --> 00:22:03,240
Uh... Uncle.

425
00:22:03,949 --> 00:22:05,617
Let’s just go with the plug.

426
00:22:06,910 --> 00:22:08,787
Just get the patch.

427
00:22:08,787 --> 00:22:10,455
It’s fine. It’s on me.

428
00:22:10,789 --> 00:22:12,416
I have the money, Uncle.

429
00:22:13,041 --> 00:22:14,501
Tell you what.

430
00:22:15,419 --> 00:22:18,714
Just keep an eye on
the shop for me.

431
00:22:18,714 --> 00:22:22,467
While your Aunt Mercy and
I are gone, you know,

432
00:22:22,467 --> 00:22:24,261
just to be safe.

433
00:22:24,261 --> 00:22:26,471
Alright, Uncle. Thank you.

434
00:22:27,222 --> 00:22:29,891
But so I'm not too
much of a bother,

435
00:22:29,891 --> 00:22:31,768
let me help you with that.

436
00:22:36,690 --> 00:22:37,524
Here! Right here!

437
00:22:37,524 --> 00:22:39,735
Right here will do!

438
00:22:40,736 --> 00:22:42,612
Ma'am, just pay me in
cash, including the tip.

439
00:22:43,405 --> 00:22:45,574
And who said you’re
getting a tip?

440
00:22:45,574 --> 00:22:47,075
My knee almost got hit

441
00:22:47,075 --> 00:22:49,578
while you were weaving
through those jeeps earlier.

442
00:22:49,578 --> 00:22:52,205
Besides, I'm paying via e-wallet.

443
00:22:52,873 --> 00:22:56,043
But I have to pay a fee when
I cash that out at the store.

444
00:22:56,418 --> 00:22:58,295
So, you’re going to ask every
passenger who uses e-wallet

445
00:22:58,295 --> 00:22:59,796
for a cash-out fee?

446
00:23:00,422 --> 00:23:02,382
Instead of three days in Bali,

447
00:23:02,382 --> 00:23:04,384
why don't we make it a week?

448
00:23:04,384 --> 00:23:05,969
- What do you think?
- That could work.

449
00:23:05,969 --> 00:23:07,471
But wait...

450
00:23:07,471 --> 00:23:09,723
Do you think we can get
Celine to come with us?

451
00:23:09,973 --> 00:23:11,350
Won't the karma get to you?

452
00:23:11,350 --> 00:23:14,061
This is a total scam.
Maybe I should report you.

453
00:23:15,228 --> 00:23:16,855
Do whatever you want.

454
00:23:16,855 --> 00:23:19,066
Traffic is a nightmare and
you've got no consideration.

455
00:23:19,524 --> 00:23:21,276
- The nerve of you!
- I'm just gonna go eat.

456
00:23:21,276 --> 00:23:23,070
I hope you choke!

457
00:23:23,362 --> 00:23:25,739
It seems like she's
paying off a debt first.

458
00:23:25,739 --> 00:23:26,740
I don't know with her.
I'm confused.

459
00:23:27,199 --> 00:23:27,699
Right?

460
00:23:28,241 --> 00:23:29,618
[gunshots]

461
00:23:34,956 --> 00:23:38,752
At least Marco is careful
and smells nice.

462
00:23:47,552 --> 00:23:48,887
Boss...

463
00:23:48,887 --> 00:23:50,555
One of them is missing.

464
00:23:51,973 --> 00:23:54,267
The target, Celine de Vera.

465
00:23:54,851 --> 00:23:57,646
Once I have the hard drives,
I'll head straight there.

466
00:23:58,230 --> 00:24:00,107
I just followed your plan.

467
00:24:06,113 --> 00:24:07,572
Hey, come back here!

468
00:24:09,408 --> 00:24:10,659
Get back here!

469
00:24:12,494 --> 00:24:13,412
Help!

470
00:24:16,081 --> 00:24:16,915
Marco, Marco!

471
00:24:16,915 --> 00:24:17,916
Marco, please!

472
00:24:17,916 --> 00:24:19,584
Let’s go! There’s a killer inside!

473
00:24:19,584 --> 00:24:20,335
What killer?

474
00:24:20,335 --> 00:24:23,088
There’s a killer inside! Please!

475
00:24:57,706 --> 00:25:00,208
From the way she's
holding onto me,

476
00:25:03,837 --> 00:25:06,381
and how fast her heart is beating,

477
00:25:09,342 --> 00:25:11,386
I can feel that this is real.

478
00:25:13,889 --> 00:25:16,433
And I can't just turn
my back on her.

479
00:25:34,784 --> 00:25:35,911
We're here?

480
00:25:35,911 --> 00:25:38,497
This is the closest
place we can hide.

481
00:25:39,998 --> 00:25:42,626
Aunt Mercy and her
family are on vacation.

482
00:25:42,626 --> 00:25:44,211
No one else will get
dragged into this.

483
00:25:44,586 --> 00:25:46,755
Didn't you say you
worked in Accounting?

484
00:25:46,755 --> 00:25:51,760
Your only clients were water refilling
stations and computer shops?

485
00:25:52,385 --> 00:25:54,596
That’s how it was at first. But...

486
00:25:54,596 --> 00:25:55,597
I don't know, since last year,

487
00:25:55,597 --> 00:25:57,766
we started getting a lot
of international clients.

488
00:25:57,766 --> 00:26:00,227
Then profits went up,
and salaries followed.

489
00:26:00,227 --> 00:26:02,395
So we didn't say anything.
Who were we to ask questions?

490
00:26:02,395 --> 00:26:04,272
Then why don't you
call your boss?

491
00:26:04,272 --> 00:26:06,733
He might know why all
of this is happening.

492
00:26:06,733 --> 00:26:08,401
Besides, his life might
be in danger, too.

493
00:26:08,401 --> 00:26:09,861
You’re right. Sir Arthur.

494
00:26:09,861 --> 00:26:12,197
I didn't see him at
the office earlier.

495
00:26:17,661 --> 00:26:18,495
Oh my god.

496
00:26:18,495 --> 00:26:19,538
What's going on?

497
00:26:20,789 --> 00:26:21,790
What is that?

498
00:26:26,002 --> 00:26:27,087
What?!

499
00:26:27,087 --> 00:26:28,880
- They're saying I'm the suspect.
- They’re blaming you?

500
00:26:29,506 --> 00:26:31,216
The police are looking for you?

501
00:26:31,216 --> 00:26:32,634
It doesn't make any sense.

502
00:26:32,634 --> 00:26:35,303
I don't know why he would
release a statement like this.

503
00:26:35,303 --> 00:26:38,056
You know, your boss is
definitely the one involved here.

504
00:26:38,682 --> 00:26:41,560
Didn't you say he suddenly
shut down the company?

505
00:26:43,937 --> 00:26:46,523
The person the hitman was
talking to earlier said

506
00:26:46,523 --> 00:26:48,858
to get the hard drives
and destroy them.

507
00:26:48,858 --> 00:26:51,861
I’m sure all the answers to
our questions are in there.

508
00:26:52,571 --> 00:26:54,322
And if the police are
involved in this

509
00:26:54,322 --> 00:26:56,157
and I’m still the suspect,

510
00:26:56,157 --> 00:26:58,994
there’s only one person
I can call and ask for help.

511
00:26:58,994 --> 00:26:59,995
Who?

512
00:27:02,247 --> 00:27:03,623
My ex.

513
00:27:08,962 --> 00:27:10,835
I'll go through all the files, Celine.

514
00:27:11,214 --> 00:27:13,341
But in the meantime, stay put.

515
00:27:13,745 --> 00:27:15,038
Just hide for now.

516
00:27:15,427 --> 00:27:17,679
I'll get back to you within the hour.

517
00:27:17,679 --> 00:27:18,680
Once I find something,

518
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:20,599
I'll pass it over to my bosses
at the DOJ immediately.

519
00:27:20,599 --> 00:27:21,683
Okay.

520
00:27:21,683 --> 00:27:23,852
Thank you so much, Santi.

521
00:27:23,852 --> 00:27:26,396
You’re the only one I can truly
rely on right now, please.

522
00:27:28,601 --> 00:27:31,234
After everything
we’ve been through,

523
00:27:31,234 --> 00:27:33,403
I would never turn
my back on you.

524
00:27:38,450 --> 00:27:39,618
[heavy sigh]

525
00:27:40,461 --> 00:27:41,820
Thanks a lot.

526
00:27:43,288 --> 00:27:44,874
I heard your conversation.

527
00:27:45,040 --> 00:27:47,015
Are you serious
about trusting him?

528
00:27:47,083 --> 00:27:48,265
Of course.

529
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,312
I trust Santi.

530
00:27:51,504 --> 00:27:54,671
Santi said we should wait here,
so that's what we're going to do.

531
00:27:59,095 --> 00:28:00,347
Are you okay?

532
00:28:01,288 --> 00:28:02,599
My stomach's starting to hurt.

533
00:28:02,599 --> 00:28:04,267
I haven't eaten
anything in a while.

534
00:28:04,267 --> 00:28:05,977
There’s some stuff
for porridge there.

535
00:28:05,977 --> 00:28:08,021
It’s better to wait
on a full stomach.

536
00:28:08,647 --> 00:28:09,814
Wait a second.

537
00:28:10,231 --> 00:28:13,193
Earlier, you knew where the key
was hidden—in the flowerpot.

538
00:28:13,193 --> 00:28:15,195
Now, you know what’s
in the kitchen.

539
00:28:15,195 --> 00:28:17,781
Aunt Mercy is my mom's best friend.

540
00:28:17,781 --> 00:28:19,491
I actually worked here before.

541
00:28:19,699 --> 00:28:21,201
How do you want it cooked?

542
00:28:22,118 --> 00:28:25,038
I might not be as good as them,
but I can make a porridge.

543
00:28:25,372 --> 00:28:27,123
No, let me do it.

544
00:28:27,123 --> 00:28:29,834
Consider it my way of
saying thanks for helping me.

545
00:28:31,419 --> 00:28:32,295
Shall we?

546
00:28:33,922 --> 00:28:34,798
Let’s go.

547
00:28:45,684 --> 00:28:46,810
Marco?

548
00:28:47,143 --> 00:28:49,062
Food’s ready. Let’s eat.

549
00:28:51,940 --> 00:28:53,149
Ooh.

550
00:29:04,911 --> 00:29:05,620
Hmm.

551
00:29:06,204 --> 00:29:08,039
Wow, Ma’am Celine,
this is a winner.

552
00:29:09,457 --> 00:29:10,834
Don’t call me "Ma'am" anymore.

553
00:29:10,834 --> 00:29:13,128
After everything we’ve been
through, just call me Celine.

554
00:29:13,128 --> 00:29:14,045
Come on.

555
00:29:14,045 --> 00:29:15,922
Besides, I’ve had plenty of practice.

556
00:29:16,756 --> 00:29:18,341
You know, whenever I get sick,

557
00:29:18,341 --> 00:29:21,302
I’m the only one who looks after
myself and cooks my own food.

558
00:29:23,513 --> 00:29:24,848
What about your mom?

559
00:29:25,598 --> 00:29:26,850
And your dad?

560
00:29:26,850 --> 00:29:28,518
You’re sick and yet
you still do the cooking.

561
00:29:28,518 --> 00:29:30,478
Don't they know how to cook?

562
00:29:32,397 --> 00:29:35,233
My mom and dad have
their own families now.

563
00:29:36,484 --> 00:29:38,319
It was my grandmother
who raised me.

564
00:29:40,196 --> 00:29:41,239
The thing is,

565
00:29:41,614 --> 00:29:43,116
when she passed away,

566
00:29:43,992 --> 00:29:45,535
I was left all alone.

567
00:29:47,454 --> 00:29:48,580
I’m sorry, Ma'am.

568
00:29:48,580 --> 00:29:50,707
I didn't mean to bring that up.

569
00:29:51,207 --> 00:29:53,334
Don’t worry about it.
You didn't know.

570
00:29:53,835 --> 00:29:56,546
A lot of people come from
broken families or are alone in life.

571
00:29:56,546 --> 00:29:58,381
This is my reality.

572
00:29:59,257 --> 00:30:02,177
It’s better to just accept it than
to sit around moping, right?

573
00:30:03,428 --> 00:30:05,847
What about Santi?

574
00:30:06,514 --> 00:30:09,058
You shouldn't have to be
alone if he's around, right?

575
00:30:10,560 --> 00:30:11,561
My god.

576
00:30:11,561 --> 00:30:13,980
Santi is my ex from grade school.

577
00:30:13,980 --> 00:30:15,774
As in, it was just puppy love.

578
00:30:15,774 --> 00:30:17,776
Plus, he already
has a wife and a kid.

579
00:30:24,073 --> 00:30:25,366
Uh, Ma'am?

580
00:30:26,159 --> 00:30:27,535
You've got...

581
00:30:27,535 --> 00:30:29,204
a little something.

582
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:41,090
[phone ringing]

583
00:30:41,925 --> 00:30:43,134
Hello, Santi?

584
00:30:43,551 --> 00:30:44,844
What's the news?

585
00:30:44,844 --> 00:30:46,429
Offshore transactions.

586
00:30:46,429 --> 00:30:47,806
Large amounts.

587
00:30:47,806 --> 00:30:49,432
Shell corporations.

588
00:30:49,432 --> 00:30:52,018
It looks like your boss
is money laundering.

589
00:30:52,018 --> 00:30:54,312
I've escalated this to my superiors.

590
00:30:54,312 --> 00:30:57,690
They’re sending a team tomorrow
morning to pick you up.

591
00:30:57,690 --> 00:31:00,235
Everything will be alright, okay?

592
00:31:00,235 --> 00:31:02,070
Oh my god. Thank
you so much, Santi.

593
00:31:02,070 --> 00:31:04,364
I'll send my address
right away, okay?

594
00:31:05,990 --> 00:31:07,617
Thank goodness.

595
00:31:08,076 --> 00:31:10,370
We can finally breathe
a little easier.

596
00:31:11,788 --> 00:31:13,623
They’re coming for
me tomorrow.

597
00:31:14,707 --> 00:31:17,502
Marco, you know, maybe
you should leave now.

598
00:31:17,961 --> 00:31:19,712
I don't want you getting
dragged into this.

599
00:31:20,046 --> 00:31:21,214
I can take it from here.

600
00:31:21,214 --> 00:31:22,674
I'm staying right here.

601
00:31:22,674 --> 00:31:25,635
I'm not leaving until
I'm sure you’re safe.

602
00:31:34,477 --> 00:31:36,980
Boss, I'm still looking
for the other target.

603
00:31:38,815 --> 00:31:40,692
You're so weak, Ramos.

604
00:31:41,359 --> 00:31:42,777
How am I supposed
to bring you along

605
00:31:42,777 --> 00:31:46,072
when I move my operations
if you're like that?

606
00:31:46,698 --> 00:31:49,617
Boss, I had no idea someone
would help her escape.

607
00:31:50,702 --> 00:31:52,787
I already threw Celine under
the bus with the police.

608
00:31:53,121 --> 00:31:55,456
I've already put a
bounty on her head.

609
00:31:55,874 --> 00:31:57,000
Here.

610
00:31:58,459 --> 00:32:00,336
That's the last time
I’m helping you.

611
00:32:01,462 --> 00:32:03,590
That came from my
contact in the department.

612
00:32:05,341 --> 00:32:09,012
That’s the motorcycle they
used to leave the office.

613
00:32:15,935 --> 00:32:17,770
What are you smiling about?

614
00:32:18,229 --> 00:32:20,023
Boss, this is perfect.

615
00:32:20,648 --> 00:32:22,233
I know this motorcycle.

616
00:32:22,233 --> 00:32:24,402
I'm sure our problem
is as good as solved.

617
00:32:26,195 --> 00:32:27,030
Good.

618
00:32:28,615 --> 00:32:29,449
Very good.

619
00:32:42,003 --> 00:32:44,047
Wait. This isn’t a dream, right?

620
00:32:44,047 --> 00:32:45,340
I don't want to get up yet…

621
00:32:45,340 --> 00:32:46,466
I don't want to move.

622
00:32:46,466 --> 00:32:47,800
She might suddenly disappear.

623
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:50,595
I just want to look at her
while she’s still here.

624
00:32:50,803 --> 00:32:52,388
Good morning.

625
00:32:52,388 --> 00:32:53,514
Good morning, Ma'am.

626
00:32:53,514 --> 00:32:54,766
I mean...

627
00:32:54,766 --> 00:32:55,808
Celine.

628
00:32:55,808 --> 00:32:57,101
Good morning.

629
00:32:57,810 --> 00:32:58,811
Are you hungry?

630
00:32:58,811 --> 00:33:00,480
I’ll heat up our leftovers
from last night

631
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:02,523
while I wait for Santi’s team.

632
00:33:02,523 --> 00:33:04,692
No. I’m not yet... wait.

633
00:33:06,152 --> 00:33:07,278
Why?

634
00:33:10,531 --> 00:33:11,783
Uhm...

635
00:33:13,034 --> 00:33:15,536
Let me know as soon
as you get there, okay?

636
00:33:16,537 --> 00:33:18,665
- Of course.
- Just so I’m sure you’re safe.

637
00:33:19,540 --> 00:33:21,876
I’ll definitely keep you updated.

638
00:33:23,336 --> 00:33:24,671
Marco.

639
00:33:27,006 --> 00:33:28,549
Thanks again.

640
00:33:29,008 --> 00:33:31,678
I don't know how I would’ve
gotten through this without you.

641
00:33:38,226 --> 00:33:41,562
I’ll go heat the food up,
you might be hungry already.

642
00:33:43,398 --> 00:33:44,524
Hold on.

643
00:33:45,233 --> 00:33:46,484
This is probably Tonton.

644
00:33:46,484 --> 00:33:48,194
He hasn't heard from
me since last night.

645
00:33:48,194 --> 00:33:49,862
Really? Go ahead
and answer it.

646
00:33:49,862 --> 00:33:51,531
He’s probably worried.

647
00:33:52,865 --> 00:33:54,033
You know,

648
00:33:54,033 --> 00:33:55,368
once everything is settled,

649
00:33:55,368 --> 00:33:57,328
I’d really like to
meet your brother.

650
00:33:57,537 --> 00:33:59,998
So I can tell him
how lucky he is.

651
00:33:59,998 --> 00:34:01,332
Lucky?

652
00:34:01,332 --> 00:34:03,876
Yes. Because you’re
his older brother.

653
00:34:03,876 --> 00:34:05,211
Thank you.

654
00:34:05,211 --> 00:34:07,964
Finally, someone sees
that I’m not like my father.

655
00:34:11,884 --> 00:34:12,969
Why?

656
00:34:13,302 --> 00:34:14,345
Why?!

657
00:34:14,595 --> 00:34:15,888
This isn’t Tonton.

658
00:34:15,888 --> 00:34:17,056
Choose. Tonton or
the woman you're with?

659
00:34:18,558 --> 00:34:20,727
What do you mean,
"the woman you're with"?

660
00:34:22,186 --> 00:34:23,855
The hitman looking
for me right now—

661
00:34:23,855 --> 00:34:24,897
is that Ramos?

662
00:34:24,897 --> 00:34:26,399
Why does he have your number?

663
00:34:26,649 --> 00:34:28,693
I know what you're thinking.

664
00:34:28,693 --> 00:34:30,611
Just let me explain.

665
00:34:32,864 --> 00:34:34,240
Marco, what is this?

666
00:34:34,240 --> 00:34:35,533
A setup?

667
00:34:35,533 --> 00:34:36,951
You’re working together?

668
00:34:38,369 --> 00:34:40,538
- What kind of game is this?
- Hold on.

669
00:34:41,247 --> 00:34:42,498
- Let go of me.
- Just a second.

670
00:34:42,498 --> 00:34:44,333
Let go of me, Marco!

671
00:34:48,004 --> 00:34:49,213
You're a monster, Marco!

672
00:34:49,213 --> 00:34:51,507
I thought you were my friend!

673
00:34:51,883 --> 00:34:53,342
Marco!

674
00:35:05,980 --> 00:35:08,357
You really are your
father's son, Marco.

675
00:35:08,608 --> 00:35:09,901
Shut up.

676
00:35:09,901 --> 00:35:10,943
You forced my hand.

677
00:35:10,943 --> 00:35:12,945
Don't you dare hurt my brother!

678
00:35:13,488 --> 00:35:15,114
Hold on.

679
00:35:15,114 --> 00:35:18,201
I’m not done with you yet.

680
00:35:25,750 --> 00:35:26,375
Marco?

681
00:35:26,375 --> 00:35:27,835
You’re going to be
the one to kill her.

682
00:35:27,835 --> 00:35:30,463
It’s ready. All you have to
do is pull the trigger.

683
00:35:30,463 --> 00:35:31,089
Marco?

684
00:35:32,924 --> 00:35:34,634
Marco, I don't take chances.

685
00:35:35,718 --> 00:35:38,304
Once your hands are dirty,

686
00:35:38,596 --> 00:35:40,306
you won't be able to
turn on me, right?

687
00:35:41,099 --> 00:35:43,976
Let this serve as
your wake-up call.

688
00:35:44,519 --> 00:35:46,437
So you can finally accept
who you really are.

689
00:35:46,896 --> 00:35:49,816
And your place in
my organization.

690
00:35:55,029 --> 00:35:55,988
Marco?

691
00:35:55,988 --> 00:35:57,824
Marco. Marco!

692
00:35:59,575 --> 00:36:00,785
Really?

693
00:36:00,785 --> 00:36:02,787
- Can you actually kill me?
- You're a monster!

694
00:36:04,080 --> 00:36:05,581
[laughs]

695
00:36:06,958 --> 00:36:08,709
Of course there are no bullets.

696
00:36:08,709 --> 00:36:10,711
You think I'm stupid?!

697
00:36:10,753 --> 00:36:11,587
Marco.

698
00:36:12,922 --> 00:36:14,132
Marco!

699
00:36:15,716 --> 00:36:17,176
It's as simple as this.

700
00:36:18,094 --> 00:36:22,431
A couple, accomplices
in theft and murder.

701
00:36:24,809 --> 00:36:26,310
Just like Bonnie and Clyde.

702
00:36:28,604 --> 00:36:29,856
- Let go of me.
- Hold on.

703
00:36:29,856 --> 00:36:31,899
Let go of me, Marco!

704
00:36:33,109 --> 00:36:35,903
You made me believe you
were a good person, Marco.

705
00:36:36,362 --> 00:36:38,197
I believed in you.

706
00:36:40,741 --> 00:36:43,327
You’re just like everyone
else who abandoned me.

707
00:36:44,745 --> 00:36:46,038
You’re a traitor.

708
00:36:48,207 --> 00:36:50,334
After everything
we’ve been through,

709
00:36:50,334 --> 00:36:52,461
how can you still
doubt me now?

710
00:36:53,421 --> 00:36:55,047
I’m not a traitor, Celine.

711
00:36:55,047 --> 00:36:57,425
Ramos is the one
behind all of this.

712
00:36:58,301 --> 00:37:00,303
He’s the reason I
ended up like this.

713
00:37:00,303 --> 00:37:01,804
So you’re a criminal?

714
00:37:01,804 --> 00:37:03,389
You really are a hoodlum?

715
00:37:04,307 --> 00:37:05,433
The police were right.

716
00:37:05,433 --> 00:37:07,476
I shouldn't have believed you.

717
00:37:07,894 --> 00:37:09,187
I shouldn't have trusted you.

718
00:37:09,187 --> 00:37:12,231
Fine. You don't
trust me? Then leave.

719
00:37:12,231 --> 00:37:14,859
Leave. I’m not going to use
you to save my brother!

720
00:37:14,859 --> 00:37:15,818
Get out of here!

721
00:37:20,031 --> 00:37:21,199
Just leave.

722
00:37:21,741 --> 00:37:22,700
Marco.

723
00:37:23,075 --> 00:37:24,327
What are you planning?

724
00:37:24,327 --> 00:37:25,453
Are you going to go after him?

725
00:37:25,453 --> 00:37:27,413
I don’t know, Celine.

726
00:37:27,413 --> 00:37:29,457
That’s my brother.
I have to save him.

727
00:37:29,457 --> 00:37:30,333
Marco.

728
00:37:30,333 --> 00:37:31,250
Marco, come on.

729
00:37:31,250 --> 00:37:32,710
He killed my colleagues.

730
00:37:32,710 --> 00:37:33,878
He won't hesitate
to kill you too.

731
00:37:33,878 --> 00:37:35,588
- Do you want to die?!
- I don't care anymore, Celine!

732
00:37:35,588 --> 00:37:38,007
I don't care!
That’s my brother!

733
00:37:39,175 --> 00:37:40,468
Just step aside!

734
00:37:40,468 --> 00:37:41,844
Please. Please.

735
00:37:41,844 --> 00:37:43,012
Please, Marco.

736
00:37:43,846 --> 00:37:45,014
Don’t.

737
00:37:49,060 --> 00:37:50,686
You helped me, right?

738
00:37:51,854 --> 00:37:54,565
I’ll do the same. I’m not
leaving you either.

739
00:37:55,483 --> 00:37:56,525
Please.

740
00:37:59,445 --> 00:38:00,655
Listen.

741
00:38:00,655 --> 00:38:02,865
If you’ve known Ramos
for a long time,

742
00:38:03,532 --> 00:38:05,326
you know how he thinks.

743
00:38:05,660 --> 00:38:09,080
We just need a plan to get
him away from Tonton.

744
00:38:10,248 --> 00:38:12,375
He thinks I’m a hoodlum, right?

745
00:38:12,375 --> 00:38:14,585
Then that’s what we’ll
use against him.

746
00:38:17,630 --> 00:38:18,923
It’s perfect, right?

747
00:38:28,224 --> 00:38:29,225
Marco!

748
00:38:29,684 --> 00:38:30,643
Marco!

749
00:38:30,643 --> 00:38:31,936
Marco, that’s enough!

750
00:38:32,687 --> 00:38:33,729
Marco, stop.

751
00:38:33,729 --> 00:38:34,689
Stop it, please.

752
00:38:34,689 --> 00:38:35,773
That’s enough, Marco.

753
00:38:36,023 --> 00:38:37,942
Marco, Marco...

754
00:38:37,942 --> 00:38:39,860
Marco, you are not your father.

755
00:38:40,152 --> 00:38:41,737
You don't have
to do this, okay?

756
00:38:41,737 --> 00:38:44,282
Please, please...

757
00:39:10,182 --> 00:39:13,144
Before, I thought stopping
wasn't an option.

758
00:39:15,396 --> 00:39:16,731
That you couldn't quit.

759
00:39:16,731 --> 00:39:19,191
One more trip. One more fight.

760
00:39:21,485 --> 00:39:22,653
But sometimes,

761
00:39:22,653 --> 00:39:24,905
you cross paths with someone.

762
00:39:26,073 --> 00:39:27,658
Someone you weren't looking for,

763
00:39:27,658 --> 00:39:29,452
someone you didn't expect.

764
00:39:31,329 --> 00:39:33,164
And that's when you realize—

765
00:39:34,123 --> 00:39:36,917
you weren't being stopped
so you could lose.

766
00:39:39,420 --> 00:39:42,214
You were being stopped
so you could choose.

767
00:39:43,966 --> 00:39:45,217
Celine.

768
00:39:49,513 --> 00:39:50,431
Marco.

769
00:39:55,936 --> 00:39:57,813
Do you think Tonton
will like this?

770
00:39:57,813 --> 00:40:00,191
So he’ll be comfortable when
he moves into your apartment.

771
00:40:00,191 --> 00:40:04,528
The electric fan and the pillows you
gave are already more than enough.

772
00:40:05,237 --> 00:40:06,238
Oh, come on.

773
00:40:06,238 --> 00:40:09,575
It’s the least I can do for the brother
of the person who saved my life.

774
00:40:09,575 --> 00:40:12,370
We saved each other.

775
00:40:12,370 --> 00:40:13,496
Okay?

776
00:40:13,496 --> 00:40:14,789
Okay.

777
00:40:14,789 --> 00:40:17,875
My boss and your godfather
are behind bars now.

778
00:40:17,875 --> 00:40:19,585
We can move on now.

779
00:40:20,336 --> 00:40:22,213
By the way, how are
your night classes?

780
00:40:22,213 --> 00:40:24,131
They’re going well.

781
00:40:24,131 --> 00:40:25,800
And you? How’s your new job?

782
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:27,510
Well, I’m still adjusting.

783
00:40:28,260 --> 00:40:30,805
Let’s go. Tonton is waiting for us.

784
00:40:30,805 --> 00:40:32,139
Marco, please.

785
00:40:32,139 --> 00:40:34,183
Oh, sorry.

786
00:40:37,061 --> 00:40:38,479
Hold on tight, Ma'am Celine.

787
00:40:39,605 --> 00:40:41,273
Yes, Sir.

788
00:40:42,733 --> 00:40:44,235
Still with the "Ma'am".

789
00:40:44,985 --> 00:40:46,195
Just "Celine" is fine.

790
00:40:46,195 --> 00:40:47,863
Just "Celine" is fine.

791
00:40:47,863 --> 00:40:49,281
Now,

792
00:40:49,281 --> 00:40:51,992
I still don’t know where
the road will take us.

793
00:40:52,785 --> 00:40:54,870
But for the first time,

794
